# SecureSentinel ‚Äî Complete Project Technical Overview

> **Purpose of this document:** This is a comprehensive, AI-readable reference document covering every component, file, model, endpoint, database, and architectural decision in the SecureSentinel project. It is designed to be fed to another AI system as full context for improving or extending the project.

---

## 1. PROJECT IDENTITY

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Name** | SecureSentinel |
| **Tagline** | "Your Autonomous Defense Layer Against Social Engineering & Phishing Attacks" |
| **Version** | 4.0.0 (API), 3.0.0 (Extension) |
| **Repository** | `DTLshit/` (local alias; GitHub: `karthik5033/Phishing-detector`) |
| **License** | Educational / Personal Use |

### What It Does
SecureSentinel is a **real-time phishing and social engineering detection platform** that analyzes every website a user visits during browsing. It assigns a **Risk Score** from `0.0` (Safe) to `1.0` (Dangerous) and provides:
- **üü¢ Green Badge** (0‚Äì40%): Safe to browse
- **üü° Yellow Badge** (41‚Äì70%): Moderate risk ‚Äî be cautious
- **üî¥ Red Badge** (71‚Äì100%): High risk ‚Äî dangerous site (auto-blocked)

Protection is delivered across **three coordinated components**: a Python AI backend, a Next.js monitoring dashboard, and a Chrome browser extension.

