## 6. CHROME EXTENSION ‚Äî DEEP DIVE

### 6.1 Manifest Configuration (Manifest V3)

```json
{
  "manifest_version": 3,
  "name": "SecureSentinel",
  "version": "3.0.0",
  "permissions": ["storage", "webNavigation", "tabs"],
  "host_permissions": ["http://127.0.0.1:8002/*"]
}
```

### 6.2 Content Scripts (4 scripts)

| Script | Matches | Run At | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| `dialog-interceptor.js` | `<all_urls>` | `document_start` | Intercepts alert/confirm/prompt dialogs |
| [content.js](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/extension-clean/src/content/content.js) | `<all_urls>` | `document_end` | Scans links, adds risk badges to search results |
| `dom-popup-scanner.js` | `<all_urls>` | `document_idle` | Scans DOM for suspicious popup patterns |
| `ai-dlp.js` | ChatGPT, OpenAI, Gemini, Claude | `document_start` | Data Loss Prevention for AI chat sites |

### 6.3 Service Worker ([service-worker.js](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/extension-clean/src/background/service-worker.js) ‚Äî 477 lines)

**Core Behavior**:
1. On every navigation (`webNavigation.onBeforeNavigate`):
   - Skip `chrome://` and extension pages
   - **Priority 1**: Check permanent blocklist (instant block, no API call)
   - **Priority 2**: Call `POST /api/v1/detect` with the URL
   - If `risk_score ‚â• 0.7` (configurable threshold): redirect to [blocked.html](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/extension-clean/blocked.html)
   - Also fires-and-forgets `POST /status/current-url` to keep backend synced

2. **Blocklist Sync**: Polls `GET /api/v1/blocklist` every **4 seconds** for real-time responsiveness

3. **URL Analysis Cache**: In-memory [Map](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/my-app/components/landing/threat-map.tsx#30-191) with 1-hour TTL, max 100 entries

4. **Dialog Analysis**: Supports temporal analysis of intercepted dialogs with trigger word detection (urgency, fear, authority, impersonation patterns)

5. **Message Types**:
   - `ANALYZE_URL` ‚Äî Analyze a URL and return risk data
   - `ANALYZE_DIALOG` ‚Äî Analyze dialog text with temporal analysis
   - `WHITELIST_TEMP` ‚Äî Temporarily whitelist a URL (session only)
   - `LOG_BLOCKED` ‚Äî Log a blocked attempt
   - `REPORT_FALSE_POSITIVE` ‚Äî Report false positive
   - `SYNC_BLOCKLIST` ‚Äî Force immediate blocklist sync
   - `PING` ‚Äî Health check

### 6.4 Content Script Badge System ([content.js](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/extension-clean/src/content/content.js) ‚Äî 335 lines)

- Scans all `<a>` links on the page (`document.querySelectorAll('a[href^="http"]')`)
- Special handling for YouTube-specific selectors (`a#video-title`)
- Sends each URL to service worker for analysis
- Injects colored dot badges (üü¢üü°üî¥) next to link text
- Click on badge ‚Üí shows detailed popup with risk breakdown
- Uses `MutationObserver` for dynamic content (infinite scroll)
- **Throttling**: 50ms delay between each link scan
- **Retry**: One-time retry after 2 seconds if initial scan fails

### 6.5 Block Page ([blocked.html](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/extension-clean/blocked.html) + [blocked.js](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/extension-clean/blocked.js))

- Full-page interstitial when a dangerous/blocked site is navigated to
- Shows: blocked URL, risk percentage, risk bar, threat tags, reasons
- Actions: "Go Back" (history.back or google.com), "Proceed Anyway" (with confirmation), "Report False Positive"
- "Proceed Anyway" adds URL to temp whitelist via `WHITELIST_TEMP` message
- Permanent blocks hide the "Proceed Anyway" button entirely

