## 7. NEXT.JS DASHBOARD ‚Äî DEEP DIVE

### 7.1 Tech Stack

| Technology | Version | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| Next.js | 16.1.0 | Framework (App Router, Turbopack) |
| React | 19.2.3 | UI library |
| Tailwind CSS | v4 | Styling |
| Framer Motion | 12.23.26 | Animations |
| Lucide React | 0.562.0 | Icons |
| Geist Font | Latest | Typography |

### 7.2 Page Structure

#### Landing Page (`/`)
- **HeroSection**: Animated hero with CTA buttons
- **Features**: 6 defense layer cards with animations
- **ThreatMap**: Live data visualization (polls `/dashboard` every 3 seconds)
- **Footer**: Copyright

#### Dashboard (`/dashboard`)
- **Layout**: Sidebar navigation with links to activity, controls, privacy, and 6 feature pages
- **Overview Page**: 3 KPI cards (Safety Index with animated progress bar, Total Scans with counter animation, Threats Blocked with critical alert), Activity Vector chart (7-day line graph), Flux Log (real-time intervention feed). Polls every 10 seconds.

#### Activity Log (`/dashboard/activity`)
- Fetches from `GET /activity?limit=20`
- Shows domain, timestamp, risk score, risk level, status
- Block/Unblock toggles per domain
- Polls every 5 seconds

#### Privacy Settings (`/dashboard/privacy`)
- PII Masking toggle
- Data retention period control
- "Export Telemetry" (downloads activity as JSON)
- "System Reset" (DELETE /reset)

#### 6 Feature Pages (`/features/*`)
Each follows the **MVC pattern**: [page.tsx](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/my-app/app/page.tsx) (View), [feature.controller.ts](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/my-app/app/features/sentinel-mesh/feature.controller.ts) (Controller), [feature.service.ts](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/my-app/app/features/sentinel-mesh/feature.service.ts) (Service/API layer)

1. **Behavioral Baseline** (`/features/behavioral-baseline`): Anomaly detection visualization, cognitive load meter, fingerprint analysis
2. **Temporal Analysis** (`/features/temporal-analysis`): Time-based risk analysis with trigger word highlighting, urgency timeline, live history
3. **Neural Detection** (`/features/neural-detection`): Gemini-powered URL analysis with signal breakdown, accepts `?url=` query param for direct scanning
4. **Cognitive Shield** (`/features/cognitive-shield`): Social engineering pattern detection dashboard
5. **Quantum Defense** (`/features/quantum-defense`): Heuristic override visualization, rule-based detection display
6. **Sentinel Mesh** (`/features/sentinel-mesh`): Extension-backend sync status, network health

#### AI Chat Widget (global)
- Floating chat button on every page
- Powered by Gemini via `POST /api/v1/chat`
- Context-aware: sends current page content
- Styled as "Sentinel AI" cybersecurity assistant
- Returns structured response with follow-up suggestions

### 7.3 API Integration

All frontend API calls use:
```typescript
export const API_BASE_URL = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL || "http://127.0.0.1:8002/api/v1";
```

> [!WARNING]
> **Bug**: [lib/api.ts](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/my-app/lib/api.ts) contains a stale `API_BASE_URL` defaulting to port **8000** (the unused modular app). The rest of the app correctly uses port 8002 via [lib/constants.ts](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/my-app/lib/constants.ts). The [api.ts](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/my-app/lib/api.ts) file's [analyzeMessage()](file:///d:/coding_files/Projects/DTLshit/my-app/lib/api.ts#5-21) function will fail if `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` is not set.

