### 11.1 Extension ‚Üí Backend ‚Üí Dashboard (Real-time)

```
User navigates to example.com
        ‚îÇ
        ‚ñº
Extension Service Worker
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ 1. Check permanentBlocklist (local Set) ‚Üí if match ‚Üí BLOCK immediately
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ 2. Fire-and-forget POST /status/current-url {url: "example.com"}
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ 3. POST /api/v1/detect {url: "example.com"}
                ‚îÇ
                ‚ñº
        Backend Detection Pipeline
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ User blocklist check (DB) ‚Üí BLOCK
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ User whitelist check (DB) ‚Üí SAFE
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Built-in whitelist (~80 domains) ‚Üí SAFE
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Strict keyword blacklist ‚Üí HIGH (0.88)
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Suspicious keyword check ‚Üí MEDIUM (0.70)
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Heuristics (IP, length, chars) ‚Üí score
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ML Model (DISABLED) ‚Üí 0.0
        ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Alive Baseline (jitter) ‚Üí floor score
        ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ LLM check (if ambiguous) ‚Üí boost/confirm
                ‚îÇ
                ‚ñº
        Response: {risk_score: 0.XX, risk_level: "...", ...}
                ‚îÇ
                ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Score ‚â• 0.7 ‚Üí Extension redirects to blocked.html
                ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Score 0.4-0.7 ‚Üí Yellow badge on search results
                ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Score < 0.4 ‚Üí Green badge on search results
                ‚îÇ
                ‚ñº
        Scan saved to SQLite (scan_results)
                ‚îÇ
                ‚ñº
        Dashboard polls GET /dashboard every 10s
        ‚Üí Updates KPIs, charts, flux log
